      <item>
        <title>cannot change Qubes keyboard layout</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Sure a new bug?</p>
<p>That method is for Non-Qubes-Whonix only.</p>
<p>How do you change the keyboard layout in Qubes generally? For Qubes dom0, Fedora Template, Debian Template? The same mechanism has to be used for Qubes-Whonix.</p>
<p>Basically set the keyboard layout in dom0 and it should be automatically propagating to all newly started (and perhaps even already running?) VMs. Does Qubes have documentation for that?</p>
<p>Maybe it never comes up since users usually choose their keyboard layout in Qubes installer and then stick with it?</p>
<p>See also:</p>
